genresAdvancedInfo.name: italian jazz fusion
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Italian jazz fusion is a genre that blends traditional Italian jazz with elements of rock, funk, and electronic music. It emerged in the 1970s and was heavily influenced by the American jazz fusion movement. Italian jazz fusion is characterized by its use of electric instruments, complex rhythms, and improvisation.
